#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"Fly with a corp that <span class=\"text-gold\">turns data into "
"action</span>."
msgstr "<span class=\"text-gold\">データを行動に変える</span>コープと共に飛ぼう。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"\n"
"        Whether you're a day-old capsuleer or a veteran looking for a sharper home, Forças Armadas\n"
"        runs fleets, builds capitals, and backs every pilot with tooling that tells you exactly what\n"
"        to fly, train, and build next. No spreadsheets. No guesswork.\n"
"      "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"        1日前に誕生したばかりのカプセラーでも、より洗練された拠点を探すベテランでも、Forças Armadas は\n"
"        フリートを運用し、capital を建造し、次に何を飛ばし、訓練し、建造すべきかを的確に示すツールで\n"
"        すべてのパイロットを支えます。スプレッドシートは不要。当て推量も不要。\n"
"      "

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "You're signed in — ping a recruiter in-game"
msgstr "サインイン済みです — ゲーム内でリクルーターに連絡"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Log in with EVE to apply"
msgstr "応募するには EVE でログイン"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "See our killboard"
msgstr "私たちの killboard を見る"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "What you get as a member"
msgstr "メンバーとして得られるもの"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Fleet PvP"
msgstr "フリート PvP"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"Doctrine fleets with ships and SRP support — show up, undock, get on "
"killmails."
msgstr "艦船と SRP サポート付きの doctrine フリート — 参加し、undock し、killmail に載りましょう。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Industry &amp; building"
msgstr "インダストリー &amp; 建造"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"From frigates to capitals — full bills of materials, build-vs-buy, and "
"shared projects."
msgstr "フリゲートから capital まで — 完全な部品表、建造 vs 購入の比較、共有プロジェクト。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "New-pilot friendly"
msgstr "新規パイロットに優しい"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"A guided skill path, starter doctrines, and patient people. Alpha clones "
"welcome."
msgstr "ガイド付きのスキルパス、初心者向けの doctrine、そして辛抱強い仲間たち。Alpha クローンも歓迎です。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Tools that help"
msgstr "役立つツール"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"This very platform: \"can I fly this?\", what to train, and where the corp "
"needs you."
msgstr "まさにこのプラットフォーム。「これに乗れるか？」、何をトレーニングすべきか、そして corp がどこであなたを必要としているか。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "How to join"
msgstr "参加方法"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Log in with EVE SSO.</span> We only ever read "
"public data to start — no password is stored."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">EVE SSO "
"でログイン。</span>最初に読み取るのは公開データだけです。パスワードは保存されません。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Get a personalised plan.</span> The app shows your "
"readiness and a starter skill path the moment you connect."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-"
"ink\">パーソナライズされたプランを入手。</span>接続した瞬間に、あなたの準備状況と初心者向けのスキルパスが表示されます。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">Talk to a recruiter in-game</span> and apply to the"
" corp. Once you're verified, every member tool unlocks."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"text-ink\">ゲーム内でリクルーターに連絡</span>し、corp "
"に応募しましょう。認証されると、すべてのメンバー向けツールが解放されます。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Who we're looking for"
msgstr "私たちが求める人材"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Pilots who want to improve — kills, skills, or ISK."
msgstr "上達を目指すパイロット — kill、スキル、ISK。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Brand-new players willing to learn (we'll teach)."
msgstr "学ぶ意欲のある新規プレイヤー（私たちが教えます）。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Builders and logistics pilots who keep fleets supplied."
msgstr "fleet への補給を支える生産者や輸送パイロット。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "People who show up and communicate. Drama-free."
msgstr "ちゃんと顔を出してコミュニケーションできる人。もめ事はなしで。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "The veteran's survival guide"
msgstr "ベテランのサバイバルガイド"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"The things we all wish someone had told us on day one. Nullsec is the best "
"part of EVE — it just doesn't forgive not knowing the rules."
msgstr ""
"初日に誰かが教えてくれていたら、と誰もが思うことばかり。Nullsec は EVE の最高の部分です。ただ、ルールを知らないことは容赦してくれません。"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Ships are ammo"
msgstr "艦は弾薬"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Fly only what you can lose.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">If losing the ship would ruin your night, don't "
"undock it. Every hull you fly in null should be one you could replace "
"tomorrow without pain.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">失っても構わない艦だけに乗ろう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">その艦を失ったら夜が台無しになるようなら、undock してはいけません。null で乗るすべての hull "
"は、明日痛みなく買い替えられるものであるべきです。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Losses are tuition, not failure.</span>"
" <span class=\"text-faint\">Every veteran has a killboard full of "
"embarrassing losses; that's how we all learned. Read your loss, pick one "
"thing you'd do differently, and move on.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">損失は失敗ではなく授業料。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">どのベテランの killboard "
"にも恥ずかしい損失がずらりと並んでいます。そうやって皆学んできました。自分の loss "
"を振り返り、次に変えるべき点を一つ選んで、前に進みましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Insurance and SRP soften losses.</span>"
" <span class=\"text-faint\">Buy platinum insurance <em>before</em> you "
"undock (right-click your ship → Insurance) — it pays back a chunk of the "
"hull, never the modules. Fly the corp's doctrine fit (our standard, pre-"
"approved fittings) on an official fleet and the Ship Replacement Program "
"pays you back too — just file your claim after.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">保険と SRP は損失を和らげます。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">undock する<em>前</em>にプラチナ保険を購入しましょう（艦を右クリック → "
"Insurance）。hull の一部は払い戻されますが、module は対象外です。公式 fleet で corp の doctrine "
"fit（標準の承認済み fitting）に乗れば、Ship Replacement Program "
"からも払い戻されます。後で申請するだけです。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Keep your combat clone cheap.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">When your pod dies, the implants in your head die"
" with it. Save the shiny sets for a jump clone — a spare body you can swap "
"into; ask a vet to help you set one up.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">戦闘用クローンは安く保とう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">pod が破壊されると、頭の中の implant も一緒に失われます。高価なセットは jump clone "
"用に取っておきましょう。乗り換えられる予備の体のことです。設定はベテランに手伝ってもらいましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Local and d-scan are your radar"
msgstr "local と d-scan があなたのレーダー"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Watch local chat always.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">In nullsec everyone in the system shows in local's "
"pilot list the moment they arrive. Keep it visible, and treat any name you "
"don't recognise as a hunter until proven otherwise.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">常に local チャットを見よう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">nullsec では、システムに入った瞬間に全員が local "
"のパイロット一覧に表示されます。常に表示しておき、見覚えのない名前は、そうでないと分かるまでハンターとみなしましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Make d-scan a reflex.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">The directional scanner (default V) shows most ships "
"and probes within ~14 AU — but not cloaked ships or Combat Recon cruisers, "
"so a clear scan is never a promise. Hit it every few seconds while running "
"sites or mining; combat probes on scan means align out and leave now.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">d-scan を反射的に。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">directional scanner（デフォルトは V）は約 14 AU 以内のほとんどの艦や probe "
"を表示しますが、cloak した艦や Combat Recon cruiser "
"は映りません。クリーンなスキャンでも安全の保証にはなりません。サイトを回っているときや採掘中は数秒ごとに実行しましょう。スキャンに combat "
"probe が映ったら、align out して今すぐ離脱です。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Watch the intel channels.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Pilots report hostiles by system name. Learn the "
"systems around home, so a report three jumps out buys you a full minute of "
"warning instead of none.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">intel チャンネルを見よう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">パイロットは敵をシステム名で報告します。ホーム周辺のシステムを覚えておけば、3 jump "
"先からの報告が、ゼロではなく丸 1 分の警告時間をもたらしてくれます。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">When in doubt, dock up.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Docked, you are truly safe — nobody has ever died "
"docked. Tethered at a friendly structure you're repaired and protected, but "
"you can be bumped off tether and killed, so never go AFK on tether. Stepping"
" away in space? Use safe-logoff, not hope.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">迷ったら dock しよう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">dock 中は本当に安全です。dock していて死んだ人は一人もいません。友軍の structure に "
"tether していれば修理され保護されますが、tether から弾き出されて殺されることもあるので、tether 中に AFK "
"してはいけません。宇宙で離席する？ 願うのではなく safe-logoff を使いましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Getting around without dying"
msgstr "死なずに移動する方法"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Bubbles catch you in null.</span> <span"
" class=\"text-faint\">Warp disruption bubbles stop your warp early or drag "
"you past a gate into a trap — no warning, no countdown. Inside one <em>you "
"cannot warp at all</em>: turn on your prop mod, burn for the edge (double-"
"click in space away from the wrecks), and warp somewhere else the moment "
"you're clear.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">null では bubble に捕まります。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">warp disruption bubble は warp を途中で止めたり、gate "
"を通り越して罠に引きずり込んだりします。警告もカウントダウンもありません。bubble の中では<em>まったく warp "
"できません</em>。prop mod を入れ、端に向かって全速で進み（残骸から離れた宇宙空間をダブルクリック）、抜けた瞬間に別の場所へ warp "
"しましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Never autopilot in null.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Autopilot delivers you to a gate camp like room "
"service. Fly every jump by hand, and check the corp killboard and Gate Camp "
"Watch for recent kills on your route before you commit.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">null では絶対に autopilot を使わないこと。</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">autopilot はルームサービスのようにあなたを gate camp "
"まで届けてしまいます。すべての jump を手動で飛び、進む前に corp の killboard と Gate Camp Watch "
"でルート上の最近の kill を確認しましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Bookmark safes and tacticals.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">A safe spot (a bookmark made mid-warp, away from "
"anything warpable) gives you somewhere to hide and d-scan from. A tactical "
"is the same idea a few hundred km off a busy gate, so you can look before "
"you leap. Make a few of each in home systems on day one.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">safe と tactical を bookmark しよう。</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">safe spot（warp 中に、warp できる対象から離れた場所で作る "
"bookmark）は、隠れて d-scan するための場所になります。tactical は同じ考え方で、混雑した gate から数百 km "
"離れた地点です。飛び込む前に様子を見られます。初日にホームのシステムでそれぞれいくつか作っておきましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Your gate cloak buys time.</span> <span"
" class=\"text-faint\">After a jump you stay cloaked up to a minute while you"
" don't move. Never panic-warp — take a breath, read the grid; burning back "
"to the gate is often the right call.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">gate cloak は時間を稼いでくれます。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">jump 直後、動かなければ最大 1 分間 cloak したままでいられます。パニックで warp "
"しないこと。ひと呼吸おいて grid を読みましょう。gate へ引き返すのが正解であることも多いです。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Fleet up: comms and discipline"
msgstr "fleet を組もう: comms と規律"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Listen first, talk less.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">When a fight starts, voice comms belong to the FC and "
"scouts. Your question can wait; a talked-over FC gets people killed.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">まず聞く、話すのは控えめに。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">戦闘が始まったら、voice comms は FC と scout のものです。質問は後回しでいい。FC "
"の声がかき消されると、人が死にます。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">The FC's word is final.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">A fleet doing one imperfect thing together beats thirty"
" pilots doing their own clever thing separately. Odd order? Follow it, ask "
"why after.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">FC の言葉が最終決定です。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">一つの不完全なことを全員で一緒にやる fleet は、30 "
"人がそれぞれ賢いことをバラバラにやるより強い。おかしな命令？ まず従い、理由は後で聞きましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
#, python-format
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Broadcast for reps early.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Taking damage? Hit the broadcast in the fleet window — "
"that's how logi (the fleet's healers) know to repair you. Broadcast the type"
" your doctrine tanks: shield fleet, shield button; armor fleet, armor button"
" — the FC will say which. And do it when the shooting starts, not at 10%% "
"structure.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">reps は早めに broadcast しよう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">ダメージを受けている？ fleet ウィンドウで broadcast を押しましょう。そうすれば "
"logi（fleet のヒーラー）があなたを修理すべきだと分かります。doctrine がタンクするタイプを broadcast "
"しましょう。shield fleet なら shield ボタン、armor fleet なら armor ボタン。どちらかは FC "
"が指示します。そして 10%% structure になってからではなく、撃ち合いが始まったらすぐ行いましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">\"X up\" means volunteer.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">When a ping says x up, type an x in the channel the "
"ping names (usually corp chat or the ops channel), ideally with the ship you"
" can bring — you'll get a fleet invite. Never be shy about x-ing up in a "
"newbro doctrine ship; that's exactly what they're for.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">\"X up\" は志願を意味します。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">ping に x up とあったら、指定されたチャンネル（たいてい corp チャットか ops "
"チャンネル）に x と入力しましょう。できれば持ち込める艦も添えて。fleet 招待が届きます。newbro 向けの doctrine 艦で x "
"を出すことに遠慮は無用です。まさにそのためのものなのですから。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Never AFK on a gate.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">The order to jump comes with zero warning; miss it and "
"you're alone in hostile space. Need to step away? Say so on comms "
"first.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">gate 上で AFK しないこと。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">jump の指示は何の前触れもなく来ます。逃すと敵地で一人ぼっちです。離席が必要？ まず comms "
"で伝えましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Earning ISK where you live"
msgstr "住処で ISK を稼ぐ"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Ratting pays in ticks.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Bounties from shooting NPC pirates pay out every twenty"
" minutes — a \"tick\". Part of every bounty is skimmed into the system's ESS"
" bank, and hostiles love raiding it — an ESS warning in intel means get safe"
" like any other hostile report. Start with sites your ship comfortably "
"handles and your ticks grow with your skills.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">ratting は tick 単位で稼げます。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">NPC 海賊を撃って得る bounty は 20 分ごとに支払われます。これが「tick」です。各 "
"bounty の一部はシステムの ESS bank に吸い上げられ、敵はそれを襲うのが大好きです。intel での ESS "
"警告は、他の敵報告と同じく安全な場所へ退避せよという意味です。自分の艦が余裕を持ってこなせるサイトから始めれば、tick "
"はスキルとともに増えていきます。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Mine with the fleet.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Corp mining fleets come with boosts and many extra eyes"
" on intel — you earn more and die less. A solo miner in null is bait; a "
"fleet miner is an income.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">fleet で採掘しよう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">corp の mining fleet には boost が付き、intel "
"に目を光らせる仲間も多い。稼ぎは増え、死ににくくなります。null でのソロ miner は餌ですが、fleet の miner "
"は収入源です。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">PI is easy passive money.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Planetary Industry takes minutes of clicking per day "
"once set up and quietly pays millions. Ask in corp chat which planets in our"
" space are good.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">PI は手軽な不労所得です。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Planetary Industry は一度設定すれば 1 "
"日数分のクリックで済み、静かに数百万を稼いでくれます。私たちの宙域でどの惑星が良いか、corp チャットで聞いてみましょう。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Use the corp buyback.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Hauling loot to Jita through hostile space is how "
"newbros die rich. Sell to the buyback instead: slightly less on paper, zero "
"risk, ISK today.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">corp の buyback を使おう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">戦利品を敵地を抜けて Jita まで運ぶのは、newbro が大金を抱えて死ぬ典型です。代わりに "
"buyback に売りましょう。額面はわずかに下がりますが、リスクはゼロ、ISK は今日手に入ります。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid "Ask loud, die less"
msgstr "遠慮なく聞けば、死ににくい"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">There are no stupid questions.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Only silent deaths. Every veteran here asked the "
"exact same questions once — answering them is what the help channels are "
"for.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">くだらない質問なんてありません。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-"
"faint\">あるのは黙って死ぬことだけ。ここにいるベテランも皆、かつて同じ質問をしました。それに答えるためにヘルプチャンネルはあるのです。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">The corp wants you undocked.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Nobody is annoyed when a newbro loses a ship on "
"fleet — we're glad you came. Join the next newbro-friendly fleet on the ops "
"board this week; showing up in a cheap doctrine ship is the whole "
"job.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">corp はあなたに undock してほしいのです。</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">newbro が fleet で艦を失っても、誰も苛立ちません。来てくれて嬉しいのです。今週の "
"ops board にある次の newbro 歓迎 fleet に参加しましょう。安い doctrine "
"艦で顔を出すこと、それがすべての仕事です。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Grab a mentor early.</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">Ask in corp chat for a buddy for your first fits, first"
" fleet, first ratting site. One hour with a veteran saves a month of trial "
"and error.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">早めにメンターを見つけよう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">初めての fit、初めての fleet、初めての ratting サイトに付き合ってくれる仲間を corp "
"チャットで探しましょう。ベテランと過ごす 1 時間は、1 か月分の試行錯誤を節約してくれます。</span>"

#: templates/onboarding/dashboard.html
msgid ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">Speak up when things break.</span> "
"<span class=\"text-faint\">Tackled (held down by enemy warp jammers so you "
"can't warp off), lost, or confused mid-op? Say so on comms immediately. An "
"FC can often save a pilot who speaks up; nobody can save the one who stays "
"quiet.</span>"
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"font-medium text-ink\">うまくいかないときは声を上げよう。</span> <span "
"class=\"text-faint\">tackle された（敵の warp jammer に捕まって warp "
"で逃げられない）、迷子になった、作戦の途中で混乱した？ すぐに comms で伝えましょう。FC "
"は声を上げたパイロットをしばしば救えます。黙っている者は誰にも救えません。</span>"

